          <li>Companies respond by cutting buybacks (stock support loss), reducing R&D (growth risk), or taking on more debt (leverage spiral)</li>
          <li>Earnings guidance revisions downward begin cascading Q2–Q3 2026</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="muted" style="margin-top:12px;"><strong>Timing Risk:</strong> Earnings pressure + valuation model reset + potential recession fears = perfect setup for multi-year bear market in equities.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:15px; border-left:4px solid #c33; padding-left:15px; background:#ffe8e8; padding:12px; border-radius:4px">
